tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function, and mildly elevated alkaline phosphatase, which may indicate hepatobiliary or bone involvement. Triglycerides are high and HDL is low, indicating increased cardiovascular risk. Other parameters are within normal limits. Recommend further evaluation of renal function and cardiovascular risk management.
